# Production Readiness Checklist — {{ app_name | default("Application") }}

Generated by A.R.C.H.I.E. · {{ now | default("") }}

This checklist must be completed before shipping to production or submitting to an app store.
Each item maps to a specific quality gate enforced by the CI/CD pipeline.

---

## 1. Security

- [ ] All secrets stored in environment variables — no hardcoded credentials in source
- [ ] `.env.example` checked in; `.env` in `.gitignore`
- [ ] HTTPS enforced — no HTTP endpoints in production
- [ ] CORS configured to allow only known origins (`ALLOWED_ORIGINS` env var)
- [ ] Security response headers set: `X-Content-Type-Options`, `X-Frame-Options`, `Strict-Transport-Security`, `X-XSS-Protection`
- [ ] Content-Security-Policy header configured
- [ ] SQL injection prevented — ORM used for all queries; no string-concatenated SQL
- [ ] Mass assignment prevented — explicit schema/model field whitelisting
- [ ] JWT tokens have expiry (`ACCESS_TOKEN_EXPIRE_MINUTES` ≤ 60)
- [ ] Refresh tokens rotated on each use
- [ ] Rate limiting on `/auth/login` and `/auth/register` endpoints
- [ ] `bandit -r app/ -ll` passes with no high-severity findings
- [ ] `npm audit --audit-level=high` passes (frontend)
- [ ] Dependency versions pinned in `requirements.txt` and `package.json`

---

## 2. Authentication & Authorization

- [ ] All protected endpoints return `401` when no token provided
- [ ] All protected endpoints return `403` when wrong role
- [ ] Tenant isolation verified — users cannot access other tenants' data
- [ ] Password stored as bcrypt hash — never plain-text or MD5
- [ ] Password reset flow sends token to email only — no URL-leaked tokens
{% if is_mobile %}
- [ ] Tokens stored in `expo-secure-store` — not `AsyncStorage`
- [ ] Biometric unlock implemented for sensitive screens
{% endif %}

---

## 3. Data Integrity

- [ ] All database models have `primary_key=True` column
- [ ] Foreign key constraints defined in models
- [ ] Alembic migration generated and tested: `alembic upgrade head` runs clean
- [ ] Soft-delete implemented (or hard-delete with cascade)
- [ ] Timestamps (`created_at`, `updated_at`) on all tables
- [ ] Database indexes on foreign keys and commonly-filtered columns
- [ ] Pagination implemented on all list endpoints (`?page=&per_page=`)
- [ ] Input validation via Pydantic schemas — all fields typed and constrained

---

## 4. Testing

- [ ] Unit tests: `pytest tests/ -q` passes — ≥80% coverage
- [ ] Integration tests: all CRUD routes tested with real DB
- [ ] Auth flow E2E: login → token → protected route → logout tested
- [ ] Tenant isolation test passes
- [ ] Security tests (OWASP): `pytest tests/test_security_owasp.py` passes
- [ ] Frontend component tests: `npm test -- --coverage` passes (≥75% line coverage)
- [ ] Accessibility tests: `npm run test:a11y` — zero axe violations
- [ ] E2E tests: `npx playwright test` passes on Chromium, Firefox, Mobile Chrome
{% if is_mobile %}
- [ ] React Native tests: `yarn test` passes in CI
- [ ] Manual test on physical iOS and Android device
{% endif %}
- [ ] Smoke test: `k6 run tests/load/k6_smoke.js` — all checks pass, p95 < 500ms

---

## 5. Performance

- [ ] Load test: `k6 run tests/load/k6_load.js` — p95 < 1000ms at 100 VUs
- [ ] API response times < 200ms for p50, < 500ms for p95 on all endpoints
- [ ] Database queries use `EXPLAIN` — no sequential scans on large tables
- [ ] Pagination prevents unbounded queries
- [ ] Docker `HEALTHCHECK` instruction present in `Dockerfile`
- [ ] Connection pooling configured (`SQLALCHEMY_POOL_SIZE`)
{% if has_frontend %}
- [ ] Lighthouse score ≥ 90 on Performance, Accessibility, Best Practices, SEO
- [ ] All images use `next/image` for lazy loading and WebP conversion
- [ ] Bundle size < 200kb gzipped (check with `npx next-bundle-analyzer`)
{% endif %}
{% if is_mobile %}
- [ ] App launch time < 2s on mid-range device
- [ ] No memory leaks detected (Flipper memory profiler)
- [ ] FlatList used for all lists > 20 items (not ScrollView + map)
{% endif %}

---

## 6. Accessibility (WCAG 2.1 AA)

{% if has_frontend %}
- [ ] All interactive elements have accessible labels (`aria-label`, `aria-describedby`)
- [ ] Color contrast ratio ≥ 4.5:1 for normal text, ≥ 3:1 for large text
- [ ] Keyboard navigation works for all form fields and buttons
- [ ] Screen reader test (VoiceOver on Safari, NVDA on Firefox)
- [ ] No keyboard traps
- [ ] Focus indicators visible
- [ ] Form fields have associated `<label>` elements
- [ ] Error messages associated with input via `aria-describedby`
{% endif %}
{% if is_mobile %}
- [ ] All touchable elements have `accessibilityLabel` and `accessibilityHint`
- [ ] Minimum touch target size 44×44pt
- [ ] VoiceOver (iOS) and TalkBack (Android) navigation tested
- [ ] Dynamic text size supported (respects system font size)
{% endif %}

---

## 7. Error Handling

- [ ] Global exception handler returns consistent JSON error format
- [ ] `404` handler returns JSON `{"error": "not_found"}` (not HTML)
- [ ] `422` validation errors include field-level detail
- [ ] `500` errors never expose stack traces to clients
- [ ] Errors logged with structured logging (JSON format, correlation ID)
- [ ] All external service calls have timeout + retry + circuit breaker
{% if has_frontend %}
- [ ] Next.js `error.tsx` and `not-found.tsx` present
- [ ] Loading states shown during async operations (Skeleton or spinner)
- [ ] Toast/snackbar for user-facing error messages
{% endif %}
{% if is_mobile %}
- [ ] Offline state handled gracefully (error boundary + retry button)
- [ ] Network error shows banner, not crash
{% endif %}

---

## 8. CI/CD

- [ ] GitHub Actions workflow runs on every PR: lint, test, build
- [ ] `main` branch protected — no direct pushes, PR reviews required
- [ ] Secrets stored in GitHub Secrets — not in workflow YAML
- [ ] Docker build succeeds: `docker build -t app .`
- [ ] Docker image health check passes
- [ ] Staging deploy works end-to-end before production deploy
- [ ] Rollback procedure documented

---

## 9. Environment Configuration

- [ ] All environment variables documented in `.env.example`
- [ ] No hardcoded URLs — all use env vars (`API_BASE_URL`, `DATABASE_URL`, etc.)
- [ ] `DEBUG=false` in production
- [ ] `SECRET_KEY` is a random 32-byte value — not a default
- [ ] Database URL uses SSL (`?sslmode=require` for PostgreSQL)
- [ ] Log level set to `INFO` in production (not `DEBUG`)

